WEBVTT

00:03.250 --> 00:07.210
Dre: After 20 years of marriage
and 5 beautiful kids,

00:07.210 --> 00:09.380
Bow and I had hit
a rough patch...

00:09.380 --> 00:12.290
[ Rainbow sighs ]
You know what?

00:12.290 --> 00:16.710
I am...
starting to realize

00:16.710 --> 00:20.250
that you and I see the world
differently.

00:21.880 --> 00:26.500
...which, over time,
had gotten worse...

00:26.500 --> 00:28.830
[ Sighs ]

00:28.830 --> 00:30.620
I think we need space.

00:32.040 --> 00:34.420
I think you're right.

00:34.420 --> 00:37.250
...until finally...

00:37.250 --> 00:40.000
I think we need more
than just space.

00:41.750 --> 00:44.000
I think so, too.

00:46.210 --> 00:47.960
How the hell
did we get here?

00:50.080 --> 00:52.210
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't know.

00:52.210 --> 00:59.830
♪♪

00:59.830 --> 01:00.830
[ Door closes ]

01:03.710 --> 01:05.920
♪♪

01:05.920 --> 01:07.710
-Hello, my darling.
-Hi!

01:07.710 --> 01:10.420
Rainbow: So Dre and I were
trying to lead separate lives.

01:10.420 --> 01:13.210
But when your lives
are as intertwined as ours,

01:13.210 --> 01:15.250
being separate isn't so easy.

01:15.250 --> 01:17.120
You're not seriously
considering

01:17.120 --> 01:19.380
leasing that house
on Coldwater.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.170
You mean my dream house
in the hills?

01:21.170 --> 01:23.080
Yes, I seriously am.

01:23.080 --> 01:25.210
It's a terrible house
for children.

01:25.210 --> 01:27.000
What are you talking about?
The kids loved it.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.210
I don't know
about a glass house, guys.

01:30.210 --> 01:32.420
I've already seen five birds
kill themselves

01:32.420 --> 01:33.710
by running into a window.

01:33.710 --> 01:34.460
[ Bird thuds ]

01:34.460 --> 01:37.040
Oh. Six.

01:37.040 --> 01:39.250
Uh, can somebody
help me get down?

01:39.250 --> 01:40.670
Yes, neighbors.

01:40.670 --> 01:42.620
Pretend I'm not watching.

01:42.620 --> 01:44.830
Live your lives.

01:44.830 --> 01:47.040
Huh.
Wonder what this does.

01:47.040 --> 01:48.920
[ Remote clicks ]

01:48.920 --> 01:50.880
[ Gasps ] Devante!

01:50.880 --> 01:52.420
Diane liked it.

01:52.420 --> 01:53.750
I'm not comfortable
with my toddler

01:53.750 --> 01:56.250
wandering around a house
that has an open fire pit.

01:56.250 --> 01:57.620
Fire pit?

01:57.620 --> 01:59.540
It's an infinity fireplace,

01:59.540 --> 02:02.290
which is illegal in America,
which makes it great.

02:02.290 --> 02:04.250
I don't think you should
be making huge decisions

02:04.250 --> 02:06.960
that involve our kids
without me.

02:06.960 --> 02:09.920
Oh, so you don't think
I can take care of our kids?

02:09.920 --> 02:12.830
Let's not forget Junior cracked
his head on your watch.

02:12.830 --> 02:15.210
It was 15 years ago.
It still happened, Bow.

02:15.210 --> 02:16.380
Who knows the kind
of relationship

02:16.380 --> 02:18.420
I could have with him
if he was right?

02:18.420 --> 02:20.170
You know what?
I'll see you in two days

02:20.170 --> 02:22.080
when you pick
the kids up.
Hey.

02:22.080 --> 02:23.170
I don't have time
for this.

02:23.170 --> 02:24.790
It's 4:57,

02:24.790 --> 02:27.290
and I have the kids
until 5:00.

02:27.290 --> 02:29.460
So I'm not going anywhere
just yet.

02:29.460 --> 02:30.710
Hey!

02:30.710 --> 02:34.120
Who wants to play catch
for three minutes?!

02:34.120 --> 02:35.500
-Really, Dad?
-Yeah.

02:35.500 --> 02:37.460
I never thought I'd hear you
say those words.

02:37.460 --> 02:39.210
[ Door opens ]

02:39.210 --> 02:41.920
Where's my glove?
Oh, God.

02:41.920 --> 02:43.420
It's got to be in here
somewhere.

02:43.420 --> 02:45.170
I can't find it!

02:45.170 --> 02:47.420
For the love of God,
where's my glove?!

02:47.420 --> 02:49.080
Here it is.
Oh.

02:50.580 --> 02:52.120
Too late.

02:52.120 --> 02:54.670
It's 5:00.

02:54.670 --> 02:57.380
[ Door opens, closes ]

02:58.710 --> 03:00.250
I got it --

03:00.250 --> 03:02.710
"Life is a buffet.
Eat up."

03:02.710 --> 03:04.420
Uh, it's catchy,

03:04.420 --> 03:07.000
but the whole point
of this slogan

03:07.000 --> 03:09.830
is to get people to stop eating
detergent packs.

03:09.830 --> 03:11.380
Well, that's easy.

03:11.380 --> 03:13.420
Just stop making them
taste like shrimp.

03:13.420 --> 03:15.250
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
I mean, who's the smart box over
there running that company?

03:15.250 --> 03:17.460
Hey, hey, all right,
this is Bow. Let me take this.

03:17.460 --> 03:19.210
-Uh-oh.
-Hello?

03:19.210 --> 03:20.710
I'm working.

03:20.710 --> 03:23.000
Yeah, that means
I'm at work.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.620
Oh, guys, we really
shouldn't be watching ---

03:24.620 --> 03:25.670
Shut up.

03:25.670 --> 03:28.040
Can anyone read lips?
-No.

03:28.040 --> 03:30.250
But I can see
dead people.

03:30.250 --> 03:32.210
Who's that guy
standing next to Dre?

03:34.170 --> 03:35.380
Ooh! He just
said something

03:35.380 --> 03:36.830
that he cannot
take back.

03:36.830 --> 03:40.250
Crops are not gonna grow
on that field for years.

03:40.250 --> 03:42.040
[ Laughs ]

03:42.040 --> 03:43.960
-I cool. I cool.
-Shh! [ Clears throat ]

03:43.960 --> 03:46.540
-Uh, wow.
-I can't believe Bow.

03:47.670 --> 03:49.380
Jack is in trouble
at school

03:49.380 --> 03:51.420
because he left his homework
in my car

03:51.420 --> 03:53.380
and somehow
that's my fault.
[ Scoffs ]

03:53.380 --> 03:55.880
She's judging me
on everything that I do,

03:55.880 --> 03:57.500
and now she's
giving me pushback

03:57.500 --> 03:58.750
on the house
that I want.
Mm.

03:58.750 --> 04:00.080
Dre, listen to me,
your problem is

04:00.080 --> 04:02.040
that you're still
thinking married

04:02.040 --> 04:04.080
when you should be
thinking single.

04:04.080 --> 04:06.920
A single man doesn't go out
and get a sensible ranch house.

04:06.920 --> 04:08.420
A single man
gets the biggest,

04:08.420 --> 04:10.830
most baller house
he can find.

04:10.830 --> 04:13.040
I agree with Leslie.

04:13.040 --> 04:14.880
Time you got
your dream home.

04:14.880 --> 04:17.500
-I'm getting that house.
-Yeah.

04:17.500 --> 04:20.670
I deserve my 360 views
of the city.
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

04:20.670 --> 04:23.040
I've earned
a rooftop hot tub!

04:23.040 --> 04:24.330
-Yes, you have!
-Yeah!

04:24.330 --> 04:26.670
I'm gonna get
that infinity fireplace!

04:26.670 --> 04:28.580
Whoa, Dre.

04:28.580 --> 04:30.790
-You have a toddler, man.
-Come on. Use some judgment.

04:30.790 --> 04:34.290
Dre: Infinity fireplace aside,
the guys were right.

04:34.290 --> 04:36.880
I needed to start thinking
single.

04:36.880 --> 04:38.620
Rainbow:
And without Dre around,

04:38.620 --> 04:42.040
I had to get used to dealing
with the trash...

04:42.040 --> 04:43.830
Come on!

04:43.830 --> 04:45.540
...dealing with the dog...

04:45.540 --> 04:46.540
Here we go.

04:46.540 --> 04:49.000
Oh, Dad
usually takes two.

04:50.540 --> 04:52.380
[ Whines ]

04:52.380 --> 04:54.960
...and dealing with things
that go bump in the night.

04:54.960 --> 04:56.290
[ Alarm blaring ]

04:56.290 --> 04:57.790
[ Gasps ]

04:57.790 --> 04:59.580
Oh, my God.

04:59.580 --> 05:00.920
-Mom?!
-Kids?!

05:00.920 --> 05:02.500
Mom!
Mom!

05:02.500 --> 05:03.500
-What's happening?
-I don't know!

05:03.500 --> 05:05.540
-Is someone here?
-Yes? No?

05:05.540 --> 05:07.290
I mean, well, there's alarms
going off, so probably!

05:07.290 --> 05:09.620
Yes, okay. Um -- Um, yeah, okay,
everybody in my room!

05:09.620 --> 05:11.380
-Okay, come on.
-No, no, no, no, no!

05:11.380 --> 05:13.120
Don't come in my room.
No, no, no.

05:13.120 --> 05:14.330
Everybody, okay.
Go to your rooms.

05:14.330 --> 05:15.830
Spread out!
All right.

05:15.830 --> 05:17.420
They have to find each of us
and pick us off separately! Go!

05:17.420 --> 05:19.210
Uh, maybe it's only
a false alarm?

05:19.210 --> 05:20.790
Okay, yes.
Okay, Ruby, you go check.

05:20.790 --> 05:23.210
Mnh-mnh, mnh-mnh.
I'm what they really want.

05:23.210 --> 05:25.210
-Guys, it's gonna be okay.
-No, it's not!

05:25.210 --> 05:27.080
No, it is not.
Okay, everybody, you know what?

05:27.080 --> 05:28.920
Spread out!
-Run! Go!

05:28.920 --> 05:31.540
-I love you! I love you!
-Come on!

05:31.540 --> 05:34.420
Rainbow: Zigzag!
You'll be harder to catch!

05:34.420 --> 05:36.920
Hey! Hey!
Help!

05:36.920 --> 05:39.620
[ Blaring continues ]
Okay, okay.

05:39.620 --> 05:41.710
Next time make sure the door
is completely closed.

05:41.710 --> 05:43.210
Thank you. Yeah.

05:44.790 --> 05:47.000
You didn't
handle that well.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.790
[ Chuckles ] Yeah,
that's what, uh --

05:49.790 --> 05:51.330
that's what he said.

05:51.330 --> 05:52.790
I'm sorry.

05:52.790 --> 05:56.040
Just, it's a new
alarm system and --

05:56.040 --> 05:57.710
We've had it for years.
Yeah.

05:57.710 --> 05:59.420
It's the same one
I've been disabling

05:59.420 --> 06:01.290
since seventh grade
to sneak out.

06:01.290 --> 06:03.120
But you know what?
Don't worry about it.

06:03.120 --> 06:06.580
You're doing great, Mom.
I don't...

06:06.580 --> 06:09.080
believe you.

06:09.080 --> 06:11.460
Dre:
So while Bow was struggling,

06:11.460 --> 06:14.210
I was killing it
in my dope house.

06:14.210 --> 06:16.620
I mean, I didn't sell drugs
out of it,

06:16.620 --> 06:18.210
but it looked like I did.

06:18.210 --> 06:21.920
Now I needed my kids
to respect Castle Dre.

06:21.920 --> 06:24.290
Stop!

06:24.290 --> 06:26.210
Denim shall never touch
this couch.

06:26.210 --> 06:27.670
Lay a towel down.

06:27.670 --> 06:29.170
Great idea, Dad.

06:29.170 --> 06:31.210
Mm-hmm.
Except you don't have
any towels.

06:31.210 --> 06:33.380
Well, stay standing,
smart guy.

06:33.380 --> 06:35.210
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Unh-unh, unh-unh, unh-unh.

06:35.210 --> 06:37.080
What?
Buddy, buddy,
buddy, buddy.

06:37.080 --> 06:40.920
You drink that at the sink
or in the bathtub.

06:40.920 --> 06:42.580
Okay. All right.
Okay?
Thank you.

06:42.580 --> 06:45.460
Uh, no shoes
in the house.

06:45.460 --> 06:48.750
Fine. I'll go walk around
the hills, then.

06:48.750 --> 06:50.540
I'm sure somebody
will give me a ride.

06:50.540 --> 06:52.580
Uh-huh.
You do that.

06:52.580 --> 06:53.750
Not me.

06:55.460 --> 06:56.710
[ Remote clicks ]
Uh-oh.

06:56.710 --> 06:58.250
[ Remote clicks ]

06:58.250 --> 06:59.830
[ Remote clicks ]

06:59.830 --> 07:01.790
[ Remote clicks ]

07:01.790 --> 07:03.290
[ Remote clicks ]

07:03.290 --> 07:05.330
[ Remote clicks ]
Uh...

07:05.330 --> 07:07.880
why don't we
go cook dinner, okay?

07:07.880 --> 07:09.670
[ Chuckles ]

07:09.670 --> 07:11.000
[ Remote clicks ]

07:11.000 --> 07:13.380
Well, you know,
it's taken me a while

07:13.380 --> 07:15.080
to get used
to this new kitchen, but...

07:15.080 --> 07:17.380
pretty tasty, right?

07:17.380 --> 07:20.210
I'm still waiting for my turn
with the fork.

07:20.210 --> 07:22.920
I think it's great, Dad.
I-I love plain chicken.

07:22.920 --> 07:25.120
Nothing fussy.
Just hot, dry meat.

07:25.120 --> 07:27.000
Yours is hot?

07:27.000 --> 07:28.710
Hey, what did I
tell you?

07:28.710 --> 07:31.250
Don't eat on the couch if you
can't afford to replace it.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.000
Well, take me
to court.

07:33.000 --> 07:34.750
Okay, guys,
give Dad a break.

07:34.750 --> 07:36.920
I mean, he thinks
he's doing a good job.

07:36.920 --> 07:39.750
Hey, guys, can we just enjoy
our time together?

07:39.750 --> 07:43.210
[ Whispering ]
It's awful here, Mom.

07:43.210 --> 07:45.460
Jack and Diane
are sharing a fork.

07:45.460 --> 07:48.750
I mean, I wouldn't say
"by a thread."

07:50.000 --> 07:52.580
Hold on.
Dad's looking at me.

07:52.580 --> 07:54.460
No, I don't think
he can hear me.

07:55.750 --> 07:57.210
Wait, wait, wait.

07:57.210 --> 07:58.880
He can definitely hear
what I'm saying.

07:58.880 --> 08:01.000
Give me the phone,
traitor.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.460
We are doing just fine.

08:03.460 --> 08:04.750
Thank you.

08:04.750 --> 08:05.960
[ Cellphone beeps ]

08:05.960 --> 08:08.040
Can I go?
Yeah, sure.

08:08.040 --> 08:10.330
You can be excused.
No.

08:10.330 --> 08:11.880
Can I go home?

08:11.880 --> 08:13.000
To Mom's house?

08:13.000 --> 08:15.250
Oh.

08:15.250 --> 08:17.920
Well...this is my time
with you guys.

08:17.920 --> 08:18.710
You're staying here.

08:18.710 --> 08:20.460
Pops: Uh...

08:20.460 --> 08:22.460
I spilled my dinner
on your couch.

08:23.830 --> 08:27.500
So I wasn't killing it.
Neither of us was.

08:27.500 --> 08:32.500
Fact is, living together was
tough, but so was living apart.

08:36.750 --> 08:38.250
All right.
I'm going to bed.

08:38.250 --> 08:39.920
Good night, baby.
Good night, y'all.

08:39.920 --> 08:42.330
Dre: Hey. Wait a minute.
That's all you brought?

08:42.330 --> 08:44.460
I thought you were gonna
set up your room.

08:44.460 --> 08:46.330
I'm okay.

08:46.330 --> 08:49.500
But...you're gonna be here
two days.

08:49.500 --> 08:51.580
Hold up.
Mom was serious?

08:51.580 --> 08:53.540
[ Both sigh ]

08:54.830 --> 08:57.790
The kids hate it here.

08:57.790 --> 08:59.830
Not just the kids.

08:59.830 --> 09:02.620
This is on you, dummy.

09:02.620 --> 09:05.290
Nobody forced you to move
into this museum of angles.

09:05.290 --> 09:07.330
I don't know
how this happened.

09:07.330 --> 09:09.670
I was just walking up
the stairs.

09:09.670 --> 09:10.830
See what
I'm talking about?

09:10.830 --> 09:13.040
Something wrong
with that boy.

09:13.040 --> 09:16.620
Look, son.
You got two choices.

09:16.620 --> 09:18.960
Well, three choices,
but you'll never take the shot.

09:18.960 --> 09:20.960
You can go crawling back to her,
or you can turn

09:20.960 --> 09:23.500
this East German art gallery
into some kind of home,

09:23.500 --> 09:26.380
but you'll never be able
to compete with the home

09:26.380 --> 09:28.210
that those children
grew up in.

09:28.210 --> 09:29.620
Ah.

09:29.620 --> 09:32.080
Maybe you're right.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.000
But I can try.
Good.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.250
Now, where's my room?

09:36.250 --> 09:39.120
'Cause I can't sleep on a couch
with this much dinner on it.

09:39.120 --> 09:40.500
[ Sighs ]

09:43.000 --> 09:44.620
Ruby: Hey, listen.

09:44.620 --> 09:46.920
Since you're a little on edge,
I just wanted you to know

09:46.920 --> 09:49.580
that if the alarm
goes off tonight,

09:49.580 --> 09:51.790
it's because I left the key
under the mat

09:51.790 --> 09:54.040
for a man I met
at Big Lots.

09:56.580 --> 09:58.620
You all right?

09:58.620 --> 10:00.000
Uh, yeah.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.040
[ Sighing ]
Oh, Rainbow.

10:03.460 --> 10:05.380
You don't look
all right.

10:05.380 --> 10:07.540
Okay, I'm not.
I know.

10:08.960 --> 10:11.500
All this time alone,
I thought it would help me,

10:11.500 --> 10:13.040
but I just -- I don't even know
what I'm doing.

10:15.460 --> 10:17.750
I mean,
I was with Dre for

10:17.750 --> 10:19.710
[Sighing] oh, my God,
for so long.

10:19.710 --> 10:22.380
I don't even know who I am
on my own anymore.

10:22.380 --> 10:24.170
Mnh-mnh.
You know who you are.

10:25.710 --> 10:27.540
You're a doctor

10:27.540 --> 10:30.000
and a mother
and a fighter.

10:31.460 --> 10:33.750
And even though
this is hard,

10:33.750 --> 10:36.460
it's not
gonna break you.

10:36.460 --> 10:38.710
You know how I know
it's not gonna break you?

10:38.710 --> 10:40.170
How do you know?

10:40.170 --> 10:42.790
'Cause I've been trying
to break you for 20 years

10:42.790 --> 10:46.670
[Laughs] with my comments
about how bad your cooking is

10:46.670 --> 10:49.580
or how poorly
you match your outfits

10:49.580 --> 10:53.830
or that your toes
look like a city skyline.

10:53.830 --> 10:56.330
You -- You've never said
anything about my toes.

10:56.330 --> 10:58.620
Yes, every time
you wear sandals,

10:58.620 --> 11:00.830
I sing
"New York, New York."

11:00.830 --> 11:02.830
You just never got it.

11:02.830 --> 11:04.120
No.
[ Chuckles ]

11:05.580 --> 11:07.580
Rainbow...

11:07.580 --> 11:11.380
you're the strongest,
most resilient,

11:11.380 --> 11:14.750
partially black woman
I've ever known.

11:14.750 --> 11:16.540
You're gonna
get through this.

11:16.540 --> 11:18.790
♪♪

11:18.790 --> 11:20.290
Oh, sweetie.

11:20.290 --> 11:22.540
Oh, thank you.
Come on.

11:23.620 --> 11:25.500
[ Sighs ]

11:25.500 --> 11:27.580
Rainbow: Ruby was right.

11:27.580 --> 11:31.920
I am a strong woman and I need
to start acting like it.

11:31.920 --> 11:36.080
[ To the tune of
"New York, New York" ]
♪ Start wearing some shoes ♪

11:36.080 --> 11:39.920
♪ You need them today ♪

11:39.920 --> 11:41.040
♪ Rainbow ♪

11:41.040 --> 11:43.380
[ Laughs ] Yeah!

11:43.380 --> 11:47.710
I tell you, girl,
you got to get a pedicure, baby!

11:47.710 --> 11:50.330
Dre: So, Bow and I
set out to figure out

11:50.330 --> 11:53.500
how to succeed
as single parents,

11:53.500 --> 11:57.500
which for me meant
kid-friendly furniture

11:57.500 --> 12:02.040
and making my dream home
into a family home.

12:02.040 --> 12:03.830
♪♪

12:03.830 --> 12:05.790
Rainbow: And for me,
it meant doing things

12:05.790 --> 12:07.580
I've never had to do before.

12:07.580 --> 12:10.710
♪♪

12:10.710 --> 12:15.000
Dre: Like cooking healthy meals
for my family.

12:15.000 --> 12:17.620
Still can't do kale.

12:17.620 --> 12:20.710
Rainbow: And learning that I was
all I needed in a crisis.

12:20.710 --> 12:24.000
[ Glass shatters ]

12:24.000 --> 12:25.580
Jack and Diane: Mom!

12:25.580 --> 12:26.620
Diane: Mom!

12:27.880 --> 12:29.580
I know.
I know, I know, I know.

12:29.580 --> 12:31.580
Okay, you guys go in there.
I'm gonna go check.

12:31.580 --> 12:32.880
I'm gonna go check.
-Okay.

12:32.880 --> 12:39.120
♪♪

12:39.120 --> 12:45.210
♪♪

12:45.210 --> 12:46.210
[ Gasps ]

12:46.210 --> 12:47.250
[ Sighs ]

12:47.250 --> 12:49.120
Really?

12:49.120 --> 12:50.710
Everything's fine, guys.
[ Sighs ]

12:50.710 --> 12:53.790
Baby Get-Right
knocked over a lamp.

12:53.790 --> 12:55.380
Oh, thank God.

12:55.380 --> 12:57.880
I thought for sure
that this was the one.

12:57.880 --> 12:59.500
I have got to make
fewer enemies.

12:59.500 --> 13:00.960
Yeah, sweetie, we all feel
the same way.

13:00.960 --> 13:03.040
Come on.
Everybody back to bed.

13:03.040 --> 13:05.540
Jack: Okay, Junior,
you can stop flexing now.

13:05.540 --> 13:08.580
[ Strained ] I'm not.
This is how my body is shaped.

13:08.580 --> 13:11.670
Yes, you're very strong,
sweetheart.

13:11.670 --> 13:14.710
You know, I'm impressed.

13:14.710 --> 13:17.500
What do you mean?
Well, the way
you just handled that.

13:17.500 --> 13:19.790
It actually felt like
you had it under control.

13:19.790 --> 13:21.210
Oh, thank you.

13:21.210 --> 13:22.920
I actually feel...

13:22.920 --> 13:25.080
I feel really empowered.

13:25.080 --> 13:26.500
You know,
it's been really tough

13:26.500 --> 13:28.210
getting used to your father
being gone.

13:28.210 --> 13:29.960
I mean,
you know, we were --

13:29.960 --> 13:32.500
we were together for so long,
and I'm not as young --

13:32.500 --> 13:34.880
I'm still your child,
not your friend.

13:34.880 --> 13:36.880
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

13:36.880 --> 13:38.330
All right, good night.

13:38.330 --> 13:41.750
Shall we?

13:41.750 --> 13:43.120
[ Indistinct conversations,
laughter ]

13:43.120 --> 13:45.710
That's your new nickname --
baby elephant.

13:45.710 --> 13:47.960
Um, Dad, can I --
Yes.

13:47.960 --> 13:49.670
You can be excused.

13:49.670 --> 13:52.960
Actually, I was gonna ask
if I can have seconds.

13:52.960 --> 13:55.330
Same here.
Bomb dinner, big guy.

13:55.330 --> 13:57.330
Yeah, are you sure
it's not takeout?

13:57.330 --> 13:59.920
Take it easy, Zo-Zo.
It's not that good.

13:59.920 --> 14:01.250
Thank you, Father.

14:01.250 --> 14:03.040
[ Pops laughs ]
Sure, guys.

14:03.040 --> 14:04.330
Go on.
Help yourselves.

14:04.330 --> 14:06.620
Thanks, Dad.
Mm-hmm.

14:06.620 --> 14:09.670
Dre: After enough time goes by,
you start to learn

14:09.670 --> 14:13.920
that the new life you're making
just might work out.

14:13.920 --> 14:15.250
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

14:19.040 --> 14:22.620
[ Groans ]

14:22.620 --> 14:24.750
[ Vibrating stops,
cellphone unlocks ]

14:24.750 --> 14:26.210
[ Rainbow crying ]

14:26.210 --> 14:27.420
Hello?

14:27.420 --> 14:29.540
[ Crying continues ]

14:29.540 --> 14:31.750
Bow? What --

14:31.750 --> 14:33.210
What's wrong?
Is everything okay?

14:33.210 --> 14:35.670
Dre.

14:35.670 --> 14:36.830
Bow, what --

14:36.830 --> 14:40.790
He -- He's gone!

14:40.790 --> 14:43.380
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, my God!

14:43.380 --> 14:45.000
Who's gone?

14:45.000 --> 14:47.670
My dad is dead.

14:47.670 --> 14:49.540
He died.

14:49.540 --> 14:51.290
[ Sobbing ]

14:51.290 --> 14:53.750
Oh, babe, uh...
Dre...

14:53.750 --> 14:55.750
Okay, I'm on --
I'm on my way home, okay?

14:55.750 --> 14:56.960
Okay.
I'm on my way.

14:58.500 --> 14:59.710
Bow?

14:59.710 --> 15:01.380
[ Sobbing ]

15:01.380 --> 15:04.250
♪♪

15:04.250 --> 15:06.420
Oh, my God.

15:06.420 --> 15:08.620
I'm so sorry, babe.
I'm so sorry.

15:08.620 --> 15:11.120
♪♪

15:15.920 --> 15:19.920
Relationships aren't just what
happens when times are good.

15:19.920 --> 15:22.750
In some ways, the bad times

15:22.750 --> 15:26.210
tell us more about who we are
and who we want to be with.

15:26.210 --> 15:29.210
Thank you.
[ Sighs ]

15:29.210 --> 15:30.330
Don't mention it.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.210
Um...

15:36.000 --> 15:37.290
You don't have to stay.

15:37.290 --> 15:39.710
I mean,
I know you've...

15:39.710 --> 15:42.380
been here for
the last few nights, but...

15:42.380 --> 15:44.290
I want to stay.

15:44.290 --> 15:45.330
Okay.

15:47.040 --> 15:48.710
Do you want me to stay?

15:50.380 --> 15:52.120
Yep.

15:52.120 --> 15:55.170
[ The Ovations' "Take It From
Someone Who Knows" plays ]

15:55.170 --> 16:01.380
♪ You think that you're wise ♪

16:01.380 --> 16:04.420
Hey.
♪ And you're really
on the ball ♪

16:04.420 --> 16:07.420
Rainbow: So, yeah, the bad times
brought us together

16:07.420 --> 16:09.540
and we just took it
from there.

16:09.540 --> 16:13.080
Yeah, I went over
to see her, and...

16:13.080 --> 16:15.000
I didn't want to go.

16:15.000 --> 16:17.250
♪ Oh, you don't know ♪

16:17.250 --> 16:19.500
And the next day, I...

16:19.500 --> 16:22.380
I realized that I still
didn't want to go.

16:22.380 --> 16:25.880
I wanted to be there every day
moving forward,

16:25.880 --> 16:28.330
for anything that came up,
big or small.

16:28.330 --> 16:30.420
And I wanted him there,
too.

16:30.420 --> 16:33.170
I mean, I know we have
a lot of work to do,

16:33.170 --> 16:37.170
but...we were choosing
each other.

16:37.170 --> 16:39.250
♪ Take it from someone
who knows ♪

16:39.250 --> 16:41.420
You know,
when I think back,

16:41.420 --> 16:43.210
I don't even
really understand

16:43.210 --> 16:45.750
how we got here
in the first place.
Hmm.

16:45.750 --> 16:48.040
Sometimes we get comfortable
in our lives

16:48.040 --> 16:50.290
and we forget
to do the work.

16:50.290 --> 16:52.330
Think about life
as Thanksgiving dinner

16:52.330 --> 16:54.710
and your marriage
is the turkey.

16:54.710 --> 16:56.290
The turkey's
the centerpiece,

16:56.290 --> 16:58.330
but once
it's in the oven,

16:58.330 --> 16:59.750
it's good by itself
for a while.

16:59.750 --> 17:02.790
So you start to focus
on the sides --

17:02.790 --> 17:04.040
your kids...

17:04.040 --> 17:05.540
♪ You ain't seen ♪

17:05.540 --> 17:08.620
...work...

17:08.620 --> 17:09.620
house...

17:09.620 --> 17:10.750
♪ Nothing yet ♪

17:10.750 --> 17:12.460
...vacations.

17:12.460 --> 17:14.290
And all that stuff
is great,

17:14.290 --> 17:16.670
but you realize
you haven't

17:16.670 --> 17:18.790
checked on the turkey
in a while.

17:18.790 --> 17:21.580
You guys have neglected
the most important thing --

17:21.580 --> 17:23.080
you.

17:23.080 --> 17:24.790
Well, we've been
working hard

17:24.790 --> 17:26.250
at making more time
for each other.

17:26.250 --> 17:27.420
Mm-hmm.

17:27.420 --> 17:29.540
And not putting too much
pressure on it, either.

17:29.540 --> 17:32.960
Just being with each other
and talking...

17:32.960 --> 17:35.250
listening and [chuckles]

17:35.250 --> 17:37.670
remembering what brought us
together in the first place.

17:37.670 --> 17:41.380
Yeah, um, at first,
I was worried that it was --

17:41.380 --> 17:44.210
it was just grief that
had brought us back together.

17:44.210 --> 17:47.120
And I was worried that we said
some things that...

17:47.120 --> 17:49.250
were too much to get over.
Yeah.

17:49.250 --> 17:51.040
But it's like you said.

17:51.040 --> 17:52.710
Our old marriage
is over,

17:52.710 --> 17:55.540
and we just need
to focus on

17:55.540 --> 17:58.120
the new marriage
that we are starting to build.

17:58.120 --> 17:59.880
So...
Mm-hmm.

17:59.880 --> 18:03.500
♪ And messed up my mind ♪

18:03.500 --> 18:07.420
♪ Had me lying in the street ♪

18:07.420 --> 18:10.830
I'm really proud of the progress
you guys have made.

18:10.830 --> 18:14.080
It kind of feels like we're done
with therapy. Mm?
[ Chuckles ]

18:14.080 --> 18:16.460
Oh, God, no.
You still need this.

18:16.460 --> 18:18.500
If anything,
you should double up.

18:18.500 --> 18:21.290
By "you," you mean him?
"You," you mean her?

18:22.710 --> 18:25.960
♪ Just accept them
for what they do ♪

18:25.960 --> 18:29.790
So, even though we were able
to live lives separately,

18:29.790 --> 18:33.170
we made the choice
to live a new life together.

18:33.170 --> 18:35.710
And, yeah, it was going
to take work,

18:35.710 --> 18:39.290
but there was no one
I'd rather work with than Bow.

18:39.290 --> 18:40.920
Hey.

18:40.920 --> 18:42.120
Hey.

18:42.120 --> 18:44.080
♪ From a loser ♪

18:44.080 --> 18:46.000
So, um...

18:46.000 --> 18:48.420
♪ No, no, no, no ♪

18:48.420 --> 18:51.170
I got you something.
Mm.

18:51.170 --> 18:53.920
But I don't want till tonight
to give it to you.

18:53.920 --> 18:55.080
Good.

18:55.080 --> 18:56.710
'Cause I have
something for you.

18:56.710 --> 18:58.120
Oh, no, wait. Wait.

18:58.120 --> 18:59.710
Can I go first?

18:59.710 --> 19:01.120
Ladies first.

19:01.120 --> 19:02.380
[ Chuckles ]

19:02.380 --> 19:03.580
[ Clears throat ]

19:03.580 --> 19:05.210
Can I open it?
Yeah.

19:05.210 --> 19:13.420
♪♪

19:13.420 --> 19:14.710
Is something wrong?

19:14.710 --> 19:16.500
No.
[ Chuckles ]

19:16.500 --> 19:18.250
No, babe. This --

19:18.250 --> 19:19.880
This watch
is incredible.

19:19.880 --> 19:23.080
♪♪

19:23.080 --> 19:24.290
What?

19:24.540 --> 19:25.880
It's...

19:25.880 --> 19:29.040
It's just that...

19:29.040 --> 19:31.460
all I got you
were these.

19:31.460 --> 19:36.620
♪♪

19:36.620 --> 19:38.540
No, babe, babe, I can go out
and get whatever you --

19:38.540 --> 19:39.670
No, babe.

19:41.420 --> 19:43.380
They're perfect.

19:43.380 --> 19:47.790
Like, perfect, perfect, perfect,
perfect, perfect.

19:47.790 --> 19:49.540
I love them so much.

19:49.540 --> 19:51.250
Aww.

19:51.250 --> 19:54.000
Happy 20th.
Oh, happy 20th, babe.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.210
Mm.

19:55.210 --> 19:56.620
I love you.

19:56.620 --> 19:58.500
I love you so much.

19:58.500 --> 20:01.120
♪♪

20:07.040 --> 20:09.460
♪ Playing dolls
with living lives ♪
[ Door closes ]

20:09.460 --> 20:11.460
What are you doing here?

20:11.460 --> 20:13.040
What you doing here,
Ruby?

20:13.040 --> 20:14.580
What you doing here?

20:16.210 --> 20:18.420
Dre said
that there was, uh,

20:18.420 --> 20:20.000
six months left
on the lease.

20:20.000 --> 20:23.080
Exactly, and he said
it was for me.

20:23.080 --> 20:25.920
Oh. Well [sniffs]

20:25.920 --> 20:27.420
no reason why we both
can't stay here.

20:27.420 --> 20:29.250
Unh-unh.

20:29.250 --> 20:31.170
Beat it.

20:31.170 --> 20:32.500
You know,
it's been a long time

20:32.500 --> 20:33.920
since we've been
alone together, Ruby.

20:33.920 --> 20:35.380
Hey!

20:35.380 --> 20:37.620
I'm strapped.

20:37.620 --> 20:38.920
Try something, fool.

20:38.920 --> 20:40.210
I'm always packing.

20:41.580 --> 20:44.170
Anyway,
all I'm saying is,

20:44.170 --> 20:46.290
everybody's
getting back together.

20:46.290 --> 20:48.460
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

20:48.460 --> 20:50.380
Got me to thinking.

20:50.380 --> 20:51.580
♪♪

20:51.580 --> 20:53.080
[ Remote clicks ]

20:53.080 --> 20:55.960
♪ But ain't nothin'
but good fun ♪

20:55.960 --> 20:57.750
What do you say?

20:57.750 --> 21:02.250
♪ I said, Kathleen ♪

21:02.250 --> 21:05.460
♪ I won't follow you
like others... ♪
